# Validation and Test Results

The system was validated using seven operational scenarios covering both nominal and exceptional conditions.

Scenario 1 – Normal Delivery

Objective:
Verify successful delivery with kitchen and table confirmations.

Result:
Robot completed the entire workflow and returned home successfully.

Scenario 2 – Kitchen Timeout

Objective:
Verify robot behaviour when kitchen confirmation is not received.

Result:
Robot abandoned delivery and returned home after timeout.

Scenario 3 – Table Timeout

Objective:
Verify robot behaviour when table confirmation is not received.

Result:
Robot skipped the delivery and proceeded according to workflow rules.

Scenario 4 – Order Cancellation

Objective:
Verify cancellation handling during active delivery.

Result:
Robot safely terminated delivery and executed the appropriate return sequence.

Scenario 5 – Multiple Deliveries

Objective:
Validate handling of multiple table requests within a single order.

Result:
Robot completed deliveries sequentially before returning home.

Scenario 6 – Missing Confirmation During Multi-Order Delivery

Objective:
Verify continuation of remaining deliveries after a table fails to confirm.

Result:
Robot skipped the affected table and completed remaining deliveries.

Scenario 7 – Cancellation During Multi-Order Delivery

Objective:
Verify selective cancellation handling.

Result:
Cancelled table was skipped while remaining deliveries were completed successfully.
